Sentencas: Proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs), consisting of BaCe(0.7)In(0.3)O(3-delta) (BCI30)-NiO anode substrates, BCI30 anode functional layers, BCI30 electrolyte membranes and BCI30-LaSr(3)Co(1.5)Fe(1.5)O(10-delta) (LSCF) composite cathode layers. were successfully fabricated at 1150 C. 1250 C and 1350 C respectively by a single step co-firing process.
Titulo: Proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells prepared by a single step co-firing process

Sentencas: The fuel cells were tested with humidified hydrogen (similar to 3%H(2)O) as the fuel and static air as the oxidant.
Titulo: Proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells prepared by a single step co-firing process

Sentencas: The single cell co-fired at 1250 C showed the highest cell performance.
Titulo: Proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells prepared by a single step co-firing process

Sentencas: The impedance Studies revealed that the co-firing temperature affected the interfacial polarization resistance of a single cell as well as its overall electrolyte resistance.
Titulo: Proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells prepared by a single step co-firing process
